values:
Mommy is very, very sick.&nbsp; Please send one up for her.

So much has gone on today, most of it bad.&nbsp; I just don't know about anything any more.&nbsp; I don't know about myself, my job, what the hell I'm going to do if something should happen to Mom (omg, after this last doctor visit I just...*bawls*), how I'm going to balance this job and Crye-Leike and help out at Mom and Dad's while Mom's on down time from surgery.&nbsp;&nbsp;


I feel like this year is a repeat of 2002.&nbsp; Except this time, it's not my health that's in jeopardy.

I officially live in a ghetto apartment.&nbsp;&nbsp;

Seriously.

I came home yesterday to my dishwasher on the lawn, the bathroom and front doors propped up against the kitchen windows, the fridge now in the living room connected by a bazillion extension cords to Ir's bedroom, the new dishwasher next to the fridge.&nbsp; There are new cabinets and lights scattered across the kitchen in a non-assembled heap.&nbsp; We have improvised a bathroom door out of the shower curtain rod and two flannel blankets.&nbsp; Oh, not to mention the oh-so tres chic coat of plaster dust that is all over everything.

Totally ghetto.

Eventually we'll have a brand new fridge, new dishwasher, lots of cabinets, a new front door, new floors and Frank is supposed to start working on the bathroom next week.&nbsp;

Of course this also means that when he starts working on the bathroom we can't actually use it at the same time.&nbsp; I'm pretty sure that might create a problem, like when he replaces the toilet.&nbsp; And the bathtub.&nbsp;&nbsp;

Yeah, we might have a few problems.

But things look promising so we deal.&nbsp;&nbsp;

*hearts*

L~bug

My parents' house was vandalized last night.&nbsp; Some punk(s) decided it would be great fun to throw&nbsp;paint on any and everything standing still.&nbsp; So they did.&nbsp; Beige paint.&nbsp; On blue cars.&nbsp; On red brick.&nbsp; On the heat pump.&nbsp;&nbsp;

My dad is furious mainly because he just had his car in the body shop from the Corolla Incident (which I didn't blog on but to give you an idea, our neighbor didn't give enough clearance whilst making a turn and scrapped her car down the entire driver side leaving a fabulous amount of body damage) and now where the beige paint dried or mostly dried it's damaged the new paint job.&nbsp;&nbsp;

As far as the KPTPD can tell, they were the only house hit.

Mom's supposed to call me back in a bit.&nbsp; I'll keep things posted.


It's a great day to be at work.

L~bug

Okay, so apparently I'm off to buy a laptop tonight.&nbsp; Hopefully I won't hyperventilate before I make it to the register because I'd really hate to have to fight someone off whilst having an asthma attack.&nbsp; 

Wish me luck!

L~bug

Holy craptastic!

I totally forgot this was the payperiod for the three week check.&nbsp;&nbsp;

I'm rich!&nbsp; Sort of.
